\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/st_group.trace_moments}{Trace moments of a Sato-Tate group}}
\begin{definition}\label{st_group.trace_moments}
\uses{st_group.definition,st_group.weight}
The trace $t$ of a random element of a \hyperref[st_group.definition]{Sato-Tate group} $G$ can be viewed as a random variable whose distribution is given by the pushforward of the Haar measure on $G$ under the trace map.

The $n$th \textbf{moment} $\mathrm{M}_n[t]:= \mathrm{E}[t^n]$ of $t$ is the expected value of the $n$th power of the trace, which is always an integer.

For Sato-Tate groups of odd \hyperref[st_group.weight]{weight} we have $t=-a_1$ and the moment sequences of $t$ and $a_1$ coincide because their distributions are symmetric about zero.

\end{definition}
